The Youths Digest, the organizer of the Campus Journalism Awards (CJA) has received over 250 entries for the 2020 edition of the annual award event. The Editor, Youths Digest, Gidado Yushau Shuaib said this year attracted a large number of entries for 15 categories of the award. He said: “We have received 266 entries across the states of the federation and the Screening Committee headed by award-winning campus journalist, Alfred Olufemi is currently working to shortlist 30 finalists for the award. “A Panel of Judges chaired by a veteran journalist, Mallam Jibrin Baba Ndace, will painstakingly review the 30 finalists shortlisted for the winners on each category and the Campus Journalist of the Year. “The nominees for the Campus Journalism Awards will be announced at Bolton White Hotel, Area 11, Abuja on Saturday 28th March, 2020 while the finalists list will be released soon.” He also disclosed that the Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu will be the Special Guest of Honour for the event while Comrade Auwal Musa Rafsanjani will be the Chief Host. It is unpatriotic to sell 50kg local rice N14,000 ― Agric… Coronavirus: 4 Chinese nationals, 39 others quarantined in… Lalong partners NURTW for effective transportation system Guinea-Bissau interim president resigns after two days in… The theme for the 2020 CJA is “Press Freedom: Catalyst for Good Governance”. ALSO READ: Schools in Lagos move against spread of coronavirus “We are honoured to showcase and celebrate the outstanding campus journalists each year on the platform of the CJA. “In the past three years, we have remained steadfast in our commitment to nurture and showcase young talents from across the country. Join us on Saturday, 28 March, 2020 at Bolton White Hotel as we reveal the nominees for the third edition of the Awards,” he said. They will also be a launch/presentation of a book edited by Gidado Yushau Shuaib, Editor, Youths Digest, titled ‘Musings of Young Minds: A collection of articles by campus journalists, forward by Mallam Auwal Musa Rafsanjani, Executive Director, CISLAC at the event. The full list of nominees will also be published on the Youths Digest website. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! HERE IS HOW OVER 5000  NIGERIA MEN HAVE PERMANENTLY OVERCOME TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS RECENT DISCOVERY BY MEDICAL CONSULTANTS LOOK!  YOU DONT NEED TO HAVE ANY EXPERIENCE TO TRADE ONLINE,WE WILL DO IT ALL FOR YOU AND YOU WILL START EARNING A LIVING FROM TRADING ONLINE TODAY AND PROFITS WILL BE PAID TO YOUR ACCOUNT DIRECTLY. CLICK HERE TO REGISTER AND EARN